---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Breathe Easy - Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Breathe Easy - Guided Breathing Timer iOS app."
  ogUrl="https://idlefusion.com/breathe-easy/privacy"
>
  <main>
    <section class="section-padding">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-12">Breathe Easy - Guided Breathing Timer &middot; Effective February 15, 2026</p>

        <div class="space-y-8 text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">The Short Version</h2>
            <p>Breathe Easy does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. Everything stays on your device.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Data Storage</h2>
            <p>All breathing session data, settings, and history are stored locally on your device. No data is sent to any server, cloud service, or third party. There are no user accounts and no sign-up required.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Apple HealthKit</h2>
            <p class="mb-3">Breathe Easy can save completed sessions to Apple Health as mindfulness minutes, but only if you explicitly grant permission. HealthKit data is governed by <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">Apple's privacy policy</a> and never leaves your device through Breathe Easy. If you deny HealthKit access, the app continues to work normally.</p>
            <p>Breathe Easy does not read any health data from HealthKit. It only writes mindfulness minute records for sessions you complete.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Analytics & Tracking</h2>
            <p>Breathe Easy contains no analytics frameworks, no ad SDKs, no tracking pixels, and no telemetry of any kind. We do not use any third-party services that collect data.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Network Usage</h2>
            <p>Breathe Easy makes no network requests. The app works entirely offline. The only network activity associated with the app is through the App Store for updates.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Breathe Easy does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under the age of 13.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>If this policy changes, we will update this page with the new effective date. Since Breathe Easy collects no data, meaningful changes are unlikely.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Contact</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:matthew@idlefusion.com" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">matthew@idlefusion.com</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
